Meditation is 24, according to my experience and trolling. BUT. You will not be meditating all the time. Sometimes I go for HOURS without sitting once, except to change spells. I also *think* you have to meditate a full 6 seconds to get the 24 mana. So if you sit down between a battles for, say, 9 seconds, 3 seconds have been wasted.<br>
<br>
You left out specialization bonuses on mod rod 2. Ratio is closer to 3:1 with primary spec conjuration.<br>
<br>
You also left out regrowth of the grove for standard group regeneration.<br>
<br>
You also left out rain spells, and specialization effects on nukes. <br>
<br>
And finally, the biggest factor of all, burnt wood staff and boots of bladecalling.<br>
<br>
OTOH I wouldn't even include dain's ring there or tunare's ft5 thingy. Correct me if I'm wrong, but a magician getting those is a pipe dream.<br>
<br>
Here is what I currently have in a standard group. I am a &quot;well equipped but non-uber&quot; level 60 magician, with ZERO NToV gear.:<br>
<br>
C2: 11 mana<br>
PotG/Transons: 3/6 mana<br>
GoB: 2 mana<br>
Total: 16/19 mana/tic<br>
<br>
Phantom armor/transons: 5 hp<br>
Natural standing regen: 4 hp<br>
Two level regen skill: 2hp<br>
Zlandicar's heart: 5 hp<br>
Regrowth: 15 hps<br>
natureskin (if no potg): 4hp<br>
Total: 31/35 hps a tic i.e. 10-12 mana/tic (3:1 transfer on mod rod 2)<br>
<br>
Total effective mana a tic, no meditation, no transfers from healers: ~27-29<br>
<br>
I expect to have by the end of the month to have another level of natural regen, 2 levels of mental clarity, and aura of battle (should of had my third chardok thing two weeks ago, but *&amp;$# long story) Bringing natural regen to ~30-33. (I plan to raise  spell casting mastery to level 2, then work on pet hold and frenzied burnout)<br>
<br>
In any case, if noone is transfering mana to me, most of my mana goes to debuffs/buffs/transfers to others (don't think of Cydmab as a nuker, think of him as mana regeneration for your cleric) and most of my nukes come from my boots of bladecalling. But anyway, what would be my approximate maximum dps without any healing transfers?<br>
<br>
Fireshields: alot<br>
Epic Pet: ~40-60 dps (remember procs and stuns work in exp groups)<br>
Boots: 600/30 = ~20 dps (never going to be able to use these CONSTANTLY because there has to be at least 15 seconds left in the fight. So I'll give myself half credit for these. Ideally dps would be 40)<br>
Nukes: ~15 (3:1 mana efficient shock of blades, minus some partial resists, plus spec bonuses) Assume never have to mod rod others and enchanter has his epic and is shisshar'ing the pet.<br>
<br>
Cydmab's total DPS without transfers to or from the cleric: ~85 dps + fireshields<br>
<br>
There's alot of variability there depending on the resist profile of the monsters. If monsters are immune to cold, my pets dps will drop 20 points. I've also had annoying incidents of slowing monsters &quot;tossing&quot; my pet a slow, pretty much crippling him.<br>
<br>
Its very rare for there to be no transfers. Either I am moving mana to the cleric or enchanter, in which case one could easily argue I'm essential for the group's function, or they are transfering mana to me, in which case my dps goes through the roof. <p>Cydmab Promethean, Triune <BR>
Level 60 Arch-Mage, Morell Thule <BR>
Die by lava, die by flame, Erudite mages kill and maim!
